Build Requirements
==================
The build has been tested on CentOS 5.3 with:

  openais-devel-0.80
  cman-devel-2.0.98
  libvirt-devel-0.6.4 (built from fedora sources)

The sources should compile with previous libvirt versions down to 0.3.x.

Build Instructions
==================

Building from the repository (requires autoreconf):

  $ ./autogen.sh
  $ ./configure
  $ make

Install Instructions
====================

  # make install

Basic Usage
===========

The cluvirtd daemon requires openais/corosync and libvirtd up and running.
It has been tested on CentOS 5.3 with openais-0.80.3-22, libvirt-0.6.4
and qemu-kvm virtual machines.

Run cluvirtd on each cluster node:

  # cluvirtd

Fetch the current status using cluvirtadm:

  # cluvirtadm
      ID  Host                     Status  
      --  ----                     ------  
       1  nvc1                     online, local, cluvirtd
       2  nvc2                     online, cluvirtd
  
      ID  Name                 Host                      State   VNC#     CPU%
      --  ----                 ----                      -----   ----     ----
       2  demo1                nvc1                        R     5901        1
       3  nserv1               nvc1                        R     5900        5
      52  efw                  nvc1                        R     5903        0
      84  nserv2               nvc2                        P     5902        0
      89  rh5buildsys1         nvc2                        R     5900        0

